This is good news for people planning to buy a luxury car in the future. But for those who already spent huge amounts, it feels unfair. They worry that the value of their cars will drop fast in the second-hand market. Online discussions show frustration, with many saying they feel like they paid тАЬdoubleтАЭ compared to what cars may cost soon.

Experts also warn that the cuts may not happen overnight. The tax reductions might come step by step and could have limits or quotas. Still, the news has already caused sadness among existing owners and excitement among future buyers.
